This paper deals with computational models of social dialog and language understanding, which are core topics in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). The paper specifically focuses on rhetorical questions (RQs) in social media, which are a type of figurative language that requires sophisticated NLP techniques to understand. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP and CL research. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CY (Computers and Society), which are all relevant to the study of social media and language understanding.
